<subSubSection id="DCCBBC87FFC000466892F937FA838EA2" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="545" pageId="43" pageNumber="544" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="946EEF0CFFC000466892F937FA838EA2" blockId="43.[151,1437,1763,2042]" lastBlockId="44.[151,1436,150,213]" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="545" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC000416892F937FEE7888A" bold="true" box="[151,274,1763,1789]" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
SIF = 7B-B-3-2111.1000; fsp = 6.6.6; fCx = 2.1.1; fSt = 0.2; fPp = B/B/BNN; fSc: PL&gt; AM&gt; AL; Ip = 1238–1283; fD = 2H-[5-8]-8-10-8-6(7)-5; DS = 52–53; V = 49; NDV = 101–102. Cheliceral blade with 5 dorsal teeth; stigmata situated at base of gnathosoma, tracheae extend to caudal third of idiosoma; scutum nearly pentagonal, with pointed nasus on anterior margin and angulate posterior margin, with dense puncta; two AM at level of AL; sensilla flagelliform, with ca. 6 long branches in distal half, far anterior to level of PL (PSB—P-PL = 7–11 µm); onychotriches present; parasubterminala (
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFC000416A69F84CFD8289C6" box="[620,631,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">z</emphasis>
) branched; f 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC000416B03F87EFCFB89CF" attach="left" box="[774,782,1962,1976]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">1</subScript>
proximal to S 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC000416BA8F87EFC4089CF" attach="left" box="[941,949,1962,1976]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">1</subScript>
, f 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC000416BC9F87EFC2189CF" attach="left" box="[972,980,1962,1976]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">2</subScript>
proximal to S 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC000416C71F87EFB8989CF" attach="left" box="[1140,1148,1962,1976]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="544">2</subScript>
; microgenuala II present; mastitarsala ciliated. Standard measurements of two examined specimens (ZIN 9004 and ZIN 9037): AW 64, 68; PW 84, 86; SB 27, 27; ASB 28, 35; PSB 29, 29; SD 57, 64; P-PL 18, 22; AA 12, 13; NL 16, 18; NW 8, 9; AP 35, 36; AM 39, 37; AL 36, 34; PL 55, 58; S -, 50; H 52, 56; D 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC700466AFCFF7DFCE78EC0" attach="left" box="[761,786,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="545">min</subScript>
32, 32; D 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC700466B86FF7DFC6A8EC0" attach="left" box="[899,927,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="545">max</subScript>
50, 41; V 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC700466C0AFF7DFBDD8EC0" attach="left" box="[1039,1064,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="545">min</subScript>
23, 25; V 
<subScript id="0855ED49FFC700466C9DFF7DFB418EC0" attach="left" box="[1176,1204,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="44" pageNumber="545">max</subScript>
35, 40; pa 452, 430; pm 380, 371; pp 452, 437; Ip 1283, 1238; DS 52, 53; V 49, 49; NDV 101, 102; TaIIIL 119, 110; TaIIIW 16, 19.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
